stops

Class Stop

  • Object
    • Stop
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Writeable

    public class Stop
extends Object
implements Writeable
    Represents a stop in the transportation network.

    Stops are where public transport vehicles collect and drop off passengers, and are located along one or more routes.

    • Method Detail

      • decode

        public static Stop decode(String stopString)
                   throws TransportFormatException
        Creates a new stop object based on the given string representation.

        The format of the string should match that returned by the encode() method.

        Parameters:
        stopString - The string to decode.
        Returns:
        The decoded stop object.
        Throws:
        TransportFormatException - If the given string is null, or the string is incorrectly formatted (according to the encode() representation). This includes, but is not limited to:
        1. x- or y- coordinates that are not integer values.
        2. Any extra delimiters (:) being encountered whilst parsing.
        3. Any of the parts of the string being missing.
